<div id="cms-image-library" class="cms-hidden cms-panel cms-panel-xl" data-admin-allow>
  <header class="cms-row cms-space-between" data-admin-allow>
    <h3 class="cms-title">Image Gallery</h3>
    <button id="cms-image-library-close" class="cms-btn cms-btn-muted" type="button" data-admin-allow>Close</button>
  </header>

  <div class="cms-library-toolbar" data-admin-allow>
    <input id="cms-image-search" type="text" placeholder="Search by URL, alt, attribution" data-admin-allow />
    <button id="cms-image-needs-alt" class="cms-chip-toggle" type="button" aria-pressed="false" data-admin-allow>
      Needs alt text
    </button>
    <p id="cms-image-library-count" class="cms-subtitle" data-admin-allow></p>
  </div>
  <p class="cms-subtitle" data-admin-allow>
    Edit alt text right on a card to improve image SEO and accessibility — the “Needs alt text” filter shows images on this page that are still missing it. Click a card to replace it on the page.
  </p>

  <form id="cms-image-upload-form" class="cms-form cms-section-card" data-admin-allow>
    <h4 class="cms-title-small" data-admin-allow>Upload New Image</h4>
    <p class="cms-subtitle" data-admin-allow>
      This adds a file to `public/images/library/`. For a direct replacement, use the upload form inside “Image details”.
    </p>

    <label class="cms-field" data-admin-allow>
      <span data-admin-allow>File</span>
      <input type="file" name="file" accept="image/*" required data-admin-allow />
    </label>

    <button class="cms-btn cms-btn-primary" type="submit" data-admin-allow>Upload image</button>
  </form>

  <div id="cms-image-library-list" class="cms-library-grid" data-admin-allow></div>
</div>
